名聲 yaśas, renown, fame.

名臘
A monk of renown and of years.

名色
nāmarūpa, name-form, or name and form, one of the twelvenidānas. In Brahminical tradition it served 'to denote spirit and matter', 'the concrete individual', Keith; in Buddhism it is intp. as the 五蘊 fiveskandhas or aggregates, i, e. a 'body', 受, 想, 行, and 識vedana,saṃjñā,karman, andvijñānabeing the 'name' and 色 rupa the 'form'; the first-named four are mental and the last material. 色 Rupa is described as the minutest particle of matter, that which has resistance; the embryonic body or foetus is anāmarūpa, something that can be named.

名號
A name, or title, especially that of Amitābha.

名衲
A name and robe, i. e. a monk.

