Ciñca-Māṇavikā, or Sundarī, also 旃闍, 戰遮 name of a brahmin woman who falsely accused the Buddha of adultery with her, 興起行經下 q.v.

旃陀羅
caṇḍāla, derived from violent, and intp. as a butcher, bad man 惡人.

